A [[mining pool|Pooled_mining]].

BitClockers.com was created with an emphasis on performance, reliability, and user support.

Features include 24/7 Live Chat, an active forums community, real-time worker statistics tracking and mining hardware giveaways/contests.

The service was first available for beta testing starting May 26, 2011 (1.1).

##Pool Features

* Merged Mining: BTC and NMC
* Real-time statistics
* Reward calculator
* SSL Encryption
* JSON API for miner status
* Protocols supported: Stratum, GetBlockTemplate, GetMemoryTemplate, GetWork
* Difficulty: Dynamic - 0.5 to infinity in multiples of 2

##Reward distribution

* Bitcoin Pay-Per-Share: 5% fee.
* Namecoin Proportional: 5% fee.
* Minimum payout is 0.01 BTC/NMC
* Pool pays for invalid blocks.

##Hosts

* pool.bitclockers.com:8332 - Load balanced between Denver/Chicago/Zlin
* pool2.bitclockers.com:8332 - Chicago, IL USA
* pool3.bitclockers.com:8332 - Zlin, Czech Republic EU

* testnet.bitclockers.com:8332 - Development pool, only produces testnet coins.

